   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Fifteen WHERE ARE YOU?</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>IN DARKNESS Scripture: Gen 3:9; Acts 26:18; John 1:5; 8:12 The source of darkness is threefold: Satan, sin, and death Satan is the prince of darkness and the power of darkness.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Sin: a man living in sin is living in darkness.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Sin causes man to be darkened.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The more sins a man commits, the more he will be dull and darkened.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Death: the darkest one is the dead one.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The ones that are in the tomb are the darkest ones; they have no light at all.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The proof of darkness Man does not know the origin of the universe.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Man does not know where he came from.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Man does not know where he is going.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Man does not know where he is.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Man does not know his real situation.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>He is filthy, yet he has no consciousness of his filthiness.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Man does not know that he is wrong, yet he is really wrong.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>He commits sin, yet he has no consciousness of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Man turns the truth upside down.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>He takes right for wrong and wrong for right.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The suffering of darkness</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Describe the misery of a man in darkness: when a man is wrong and will not acknowledge it, he falls into darkness.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In darkness man does not know where he came from or where he is going.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>He is like a dumb fool, very miserable.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>He does not know what is the right way to go on, and he does not know where to turn to get help.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>His living is so gloomy it seems as if the day will never break.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Ask the people, If such is your case, how can you ever find happiness?</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The danger of darkness</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Darkness causes you to fall into the deep pit, death, and eternal perdition.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>How to get out of darkness Christ is the light.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The life of Christ is the light.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>God is light.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The Bible is the light.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>So you need to receive the Bible, God, Christ, and His life.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Such receiving is faith.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Believe in God according to the words of the Bible, confess your own sins, and receive the Lord Jesus as the Savior of your life.</S>
   </TEXT>
